==English==
===Proper noun===
'''Miriam'''

# Sister of Moses and Aaron
# A female given name


===Etymology===
Hebrew: [[מרים|מִרְיָם]] (Miriam), meaning 'bitter, bitterness'. She was born in Egypt when the Jews where kept as slaves by the Egyptians. Cf. [[myrrhe]]. Maria is the Greek form of this name.

